    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Chevron Corporation announced that it would acquire Texaco Inc. for about $36.5 billion, thereby creating the world's fifth-largest oil company.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Chevron Corporation announced that it would acquire Texaco Inc. for about $36.5 billion, thereby creating the world's fifth-largest oil company.</p>
        <p>The new company, to be called ChevronTexaco, would still be smaller than ExxonMobil, but such mergers are proving essential these days as the oil industry struggles to retain the interest of a stock market enamored with the New Economy. Moreover, the latest oil finds in deepwater sites demand investments that smaller companies would have trouble making.</p>
        <p>Neela Banerjee</p>
        <p>OCTOBER 15-21</p>
      </block>
